    Installation

    You can install the development version from GitHub with:

    # install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("mytalbot/tiefightR")

    tiefightR uses the following packages as dependencies (in no particular order):
    magrittr, tibble, dplyr, reshape2, prefmod, gnm, ggplot2, ggpubr, parallel, foreach, viridis, Rmisc

    tidyverse!!! Lazy loading

    Example

    This is a basic example which shows you how to compare an item with any combination of the remaining items.

    library(tiefightR)
raw        <- tiefightR::human
human_test <- tie_worth(xdata     = raw,
                        showplot  = TRUE,
                        compstudy = "LagreValenceRange_SpringSchool",
                        default   = "War",
                        ordn      = c("Cat", "Crow", "Doctor", "Frustrated", "Lake", "War", "Fire"),
                        r1        = "Lake", # change this
                        r2        = "Cat")  # change this / to multiple combis
